SIMPLE: moulinet
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moulinet
<hw>Mou"li*net</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>moulinet</ets>, orig.,
a little mill, dim. of <ets>moulin</ets> mill. See <er>Mill</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The drum upon which the rope is wound in a capstan,
crane, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A machine formerly used for bending a crossbow by
winding it up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In sword and saber exercises, a circular swing of
the weapon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moult</ent>⟦br⟧
